gomodel:SYNGO_67  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: It is demonstrated that PKC gamma controls post-tetanic potentiation in the juvenile calyx of Held. Since it does not regulate pool size (figure 5) or calcium influx (figure 6), it must regulate the probability of Ca2+-dependent fusion.. Experimental description: PKCγ KO mice (Abeliovich et al., 1993) were obtained from Jackson Laboratory." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
